{
  "text": "In this study, oregano oil showed MIC values of 0.0625 ml/100 ml against L. innocua ATCC 33090 and E. coli ATCC 11303, while clove oil showed MIC values of 0.125 ml/100 ml against both strains tested in TSB medium using a broth microdilution method (data not shown). [CITATION_1] reported similar MIC values (0.0625 ml/100 ml) for oregano oil against E. coli, while clove oil displayed bacteriostatic properties against E. coli at 0.25 ml/100 ml [CITATION_2] .",
